onyomiExamples.meaning: large fan-shaped object held by an attendant and used to conceal the face of a noble, etc.

kunyomiExamples.meaning: shade, shadow, behind (something), other side, back, the background, behind the scenes, behind someone's back, gloom (in someone's expression, nature, etc.), darkness
shadow (e.g. on someone's happiness), cloud, shade, gloom
to become clouded, to darken, to get dark, to become hidden (behind clouds), to darken (of a face), to worsen, to deteriorate, to become gloomy
to hold up over one's head, to hold aloft, to hold over something, to hold (one's hands) out (e.g. towards a fire), to cover something with something, to hold up to shade one's eyes, face, etc.
